      <hedline>
        <hl1>Shower Massage Grows Flexible</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Bonnie Schwartz</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Schwartz, Bonnie</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Teledyne offers new adjustable shower massage; photo (Currents column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>It was the early 1970's, post Age of Aquarius, when Teledyne came out with its first shower massage. After lots of imitations, the company has issued a new adjustable shower massage, from Anderson Design of Plainville, Conn. The unit's D shape makes it easier to adjust for tall and short people, and the handle has a nonslip grip. The adjustable shower massager, with eight spray settings, is available in stores, for about $45.</p>
      </block>
